  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Using Travel Insurance Instead of Health Insurance</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Greece explicitly rejects travel medical insurance. SafetyWing, World Nomads, and similar travel policies don't qualify. You need comprehensive long-term health insurance—this is the most common rejection reason.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Missing the Residence Permit Deadline</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">After arriving with your visa, you have 30 days to apply for the residence permit. Missing this deadline can complicate your status. Book your appointment at the migration office immediately upon arrival.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Underestimating Family Income Requirements</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The +20% for spouse and +15% per child adds up quickly. A couple with two kids needs €5,355/month, not €3,500. Calculate your required threshold before applying and ensure you meet it consistently.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Not Getting Criminal Records from All Countries</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You need criminal record certificates from your home country AND any country where you lived for 12+ months. Missing one of these will delay or reject your application.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Assuming Island Internet is Reliable</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Not a visa mistake, but a practical one. Some Greek islands have excellent connectivity; others don't. Research internet infrastructure before choosing your location. Athens and Thessaloniki are safe bets; remote islands may need Starlink.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

